Package: atcddd
Title: WHO ATC/DDD Crawler and Parser
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Lucas VHH",
           family = "TRAN",
           email = "tranhungydhcm@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Tools for retrieving, parsing, searching, and computing with the World Health
    Organization's Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) Classification System
    and Defined Daily Dose (DDD) Index. Users explicitly download the current
    index from the WHO Collaborating Centre via atc_download(); data are cached
    locally for offline use. Provides robust HTTP retrieval with retries, rate
    limiting, and filesystem caching; parses hierarchical ATC codes and DDD
    specifications into tidy tables; generates SHA256 checksums for
    reproducibility; and exports results to CSV format. Includes drug name
    search and resolution (with brand name synonyms and fuzzy matching),
    free-text clinical note extraction, ATC hierarchy navigation, and DDD
    computation from prescription data. The package does not distribute WHO
    data. Ideal for pharmacoepidemiology, health services research, drug
    utilization studies, and clinical data science workflows.
